To align a single item in the middle of a grid, you need to place it specifically in the central cell of your grid layout. Given your 3x3 grid setup using the CSS Grid Layout, you can achieve this by using `grid-column` and `grid-row` properties to place the item in the desired cell. Here's how you can do it:

1. Ensure your container has a CSS rule like you've defined:

```css
.container {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    grid-template-rows: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 4px;
}
```

2. Align the single grid item in the center by placing it in the second column and second row. Assuming your HTML structure is like this:

```html
<div class="container">
    <div class="item">Centered Item</div>
</div>
```

You would apply the following CSS to the `.item`:

```css
.item {
    grid-column: 2 / 3; /* Starts at column 2, ends before column 3 */
    grid-row: 2 / 3; /* Starts at row 2, ends before row 3 */
}
```

This approach will ensure the single item spans only the middle cell of the grid, effectively centering it in the grid layout.

